thread.title: Watch LSU QB Brandon Harris shake Florida sack, find Malachi Dupre for TD
thread.title_full: Watch LSU QB Brandon Harris shake Florida sack, find Malachi Dupre for TD | NOLA.com

author: Jerit Roser, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Watch LSU QB Brandon Harris shake Florida sack, find Malachi Dupre for TD
text:
Brandon Harris and the LSU passing game managed their best half thus far this season Saturday, including an impressive play just before halftime to stretch its lead on Florida.
The quarterback shook off a potential sack by Gators defensive end Jordan Sherit, kept rolling out and found fellow sophomore Malachi Dupre deep.
Dupre avoided a tackler and made his way into the end zone for the duo's second scoring connection, this time for 50 yards.
Harris completed 10 of 12 pass attempts for 189 yards in the opening two quarters.
Dupre meanwhile eased up on a career day with four catches for 115 yards and two touchdowns in the first half.
The John Curtis product caught four passes for 120 yards and two scores against Mississippi State as a freshman.
